The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, March 26, 2004 				 Generations on canvas
																								Connoisseurs of art in the city have a rare occasion to whet their passion for painting and sculpture at the Metropolitan Art Salon. Rare, because the ongoing exhibition is a platform on which three generations of artists meet through their creations to display their perception of the arts of painting and sculpture. Art lovers will be regaled by an exhibition that freezes, in a single time and space, the geniuses of the yesteryear and the masters of today with the talent of those waiting in the wings to take on the world with their idea of the aesthetic.																								Event: Paintings amp; sculptures by masters of yesterday, today amp; tomorrow																								When: Till April 5; 3 pm - 8 pm																								Where: Metropolitan Art Salon
